-- Volvo's Indian Venture to Spend 5 Billion Rupees to Double Truck Capacity
-- B y   S u b r a m a n i a m   S h a r m a
-- 2010-11-16T06:46:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-16/volvo-s-indian-venture-to-spend-5-billion-rupees-to-double-truck-capacity.html
 VE Commercial Vehicles, a venture
between Volvo Group and Eicher Motors Ltd., plans to spend 5
billion rupees to double truck manufacturing capacity to 8,000
vehicles per month in the next three years, Siddhartha Lal,
chief executive of Eicher, said in New Delhi today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
